This paper is about model compression, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on deep neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions hyperparameter optimization, which is a topic in optimization and search algorithms, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well. Finally, the paper involves building complex compression strategies using simple operators, which could be considered a topic in data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
